WEBVTT

00:01.450 --> 00:09.490
Anytime you compose a G-mail basically there's a subject who you're sending it to CCCC the body and

00:09.490 --> 00:10.900
then a signature isn't it.

00:10.970 --> 00:12.370
We're talking about signatures.

00:12.370 --> 00:13.700
A signature could be.

00:13.700 --> 00:16.300
Regards Cheerz whatever your name.

00:16.380 --> 00:20.860
Maybe some information about company maybe even a phone number or something down at the bottom.

00:20.890 --> 00:22.470
Even an image.

00:22.960 --> 00:27.280
But I don't really want to do that every time I compose a message.

00:27.280 --> 00:32.920
So Google gives us the ability in Gmail to create our own permanent signature if you will.

00:32.920 --> 00:33.880
Let's do that.

00:33.880 --> 00:37.290
Let's go up to this button right here and go down to settings.

00:37.460 --> 00:39.350
Now you should be on General.

00:39.610 --> 00:44.410
Go down down down down and eventually you will see signature right here.

00:44.410 --> 00:49.060
Now of course by default there is no let's go ahead and click here and let's make a signature.

00:51.340 --> 00:53.110
Come back up again and do this

00:56.040 --> 00:59.860
whatever you want to put down the that's a good phone number.

00:59.860 --> 01:03.480
Now you of course have the ability here to reformat it.

01:03.580 --> 01:09.070
You can add a link if you want to maybe to your Web site you can add an image if you want to it's up

01:09.070 --> 01:09.970
to you.

01:09.970 --> 01:13.810
You can insert this signature before quoted text in replies.

01:13.830 --> 01:16.750
That's in reply and remove that line that precedes it.

01:16.750 --> 01:18.640
That's an option if you want to choose.

01:18.850 --> 01:20.970
I like what I've got here I think I'm OK.

01:21.190 --> 01:22.660
So let's go ahead and come down here.

01:22.660 --> 01:28.250
Don't forget you have to save the changes if we now go over to compose something.

01:28.660 --> 01:30.010
Well there it is.

01:30.010 --> 01:34.720
Now it's not really that big of a deal I understand that but it's something that can save you some time

01:34.720 --> 01:39.290
when you're composing your messages to have one standardized signature.

01:39.550 --> 01:42.830
And don't forget you can add links and you can add images if you want.
